<subSubSection id="69D96AEAB422FFB3649DF749FAD58DC7" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="217C3961B422FFB3649DF749FAD58DC7" blockId="30.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB3649DF749FE898DBF" bold="true" box="[199,334,1663,1689]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB36664F749FD058DBF" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[574,706,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernasconii">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB36664F749FD058DBF" box="[574,706,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">bernasconii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(masculine noun in genitive) is dedicated to Marco Bernasconi, curator of the Natur Museum (
<collectingRegion id="E307F783B422FFB365B1F795FD878D9B" box="[491,576,1699,1725]" country="Switzerland" name="Luzern" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Luzern</collectingRegion>
), for his continuous support in my study of Linsenmaier’s collection, for permissions to examine 
<typeStatus id="FE7887C3B422FFB365D9F7F1FE748DC7" box="[387,435,1735,1761]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
materials during the years and for the loan of unidentified Indian specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="69D96AEAB422FFB2649DF7DDFEC08A3B" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="217C3961B422FFB2649DF7DDFEC08A3B" blockId="30.[151,1437,258,2013]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB3649DF7DDFEFC8C23" bold="true" box="[199,315,1771,1797]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB3651BF7DDFDE78C23" authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,544,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernasconii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB3651BF7DDFDE78C23" box="[321,544,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Chrysis bernasconii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB3667CF7DDFDB88C23" bold="true" box="[550,639,1771,1797]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="08845808B422FFB3667CF7DDFDB88C23" box="[550,639,1771,1797]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is the first known member of 
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB36793F7DDFB858C23" box="[969,1090,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">subsinuata</emphasis>
group from the Oriental region and with a fully blue metallic colouration. In the Middle East (
<collectingCountry id="59D479F1B422FFB36712F639FCB08C0F" box="[840,887,1807,1833]" name="Iran" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="59D479F1B422FFB367F1F639FB8D8C0C" box="[939,1098,1807,1834]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
), three species are known with green body colouration (
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB365F1F605FDF48C6B" box="[427,563,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="echidna">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB365F1F605FDF48C6B" box="[427,563,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ch. echidna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B422FFB36660F605FC578C6B" author="Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, A. P." box="[570,912,1843,1869]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="118 - 184" refId="ref56694" refString="Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, A. P. (1967) New species of gold wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Proceedings of the Zoological Institute, Academy of Sciences of the USSR, 43, 118 - 184. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1967">Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB367C1F605FBCC8C6B" box="[923,1035,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hydra">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB367C1F605FBCC8C6B" box="[923,1035,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ch. hydra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B422FFB36048F605FAAE8C6B" author="Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, A. P." box="[1042,1385,1843,1869]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="118 - 184" refId="ref56694" refString="Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, A. P. (1967) New species of gold wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Proceedings of the Zoological Institute, Academy of Sciences of the USSR, 43, 118 - 184. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1967">Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, 1967</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB364CDF661FDDD8C57" authority="Linsenmaier, 1994" authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1994" box="[151,538,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orienticola">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB364CDF661FE878C57" box="[151,320,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ch. orienticola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B422FFB3651CF661FDDD8C57" author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[326,538,1879,1905]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="145 - 206" refId="ref53582" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1994) The Chrysididae (Insecta: Hymenoptera) of the Arabian Peninsula. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 14, 145 - 206." type="journal article" year="1994">Linsenmaier, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
); they are easily recognizable by apical margin of the tergum III medially sinuate and laterally with corners, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB3667DF64DFD1D8CB3" authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[551,730,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernasconii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB3667DF64DFD1D8CB3" box="[551,730,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ch. bernasconii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB366B8F64DFCFB8CB3" bold="true" box="[738,828,1915,1941]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="08845808B422FFB366B8F64DFCFB8CB3" box="[738,828,1915,1941]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has four short, triangular teeth. Only another member of the 
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB364B8F6A9FE9C8C9F" box="[226,347,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">subsinuata</emphasis>
group has four apical teeth, 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB366FCF6A9FCD08C9F" box="[678,791,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB366FCF6A9FCD08C9F" box="[678,791,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ch. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B422FFB3677BF6A9FBBE8C9F" author="Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, A. P." box="[801,1145,1951,1977]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="118 - 184" refId="ref56694" refString="Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, A. P. (1967) New species of gold wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Proceedings of the Zoological Institute, Academy of Sciences of the USSR, 43, 118 - 184. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1967">Semenov-Tian-Shanskij, 1967</bibRefCitation>
, from Central Asia (
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B422FFB36138F6A9FF188CFB" author="Rosa, P." pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="397 - 417" refId="ref55062" refString="Rosa, P. (2019 c) A new remarkable species in the Chrysis ignita group (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) and an overview on Central Asian species, with new synonymies. Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 51 (1), 397 - 417." type="journal article" year="2019">Rosa 2019c</bibRefCitation>
), with bicoloured and elongate body (up to 
<quantity id="E63B9484B422FFB3669CF6F5FCDE8CFB" box="[710,793,1987,2013]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
). We include 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B422FFB367EAF6F5FB568CFB" authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[944,1169,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernasconii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB367EAF6F5FB568CFB" box="[944,1169,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Chrysis bernasconii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB360C2F6F5FB368CFB" bold="true" box="[1176,1265,1987,2013]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="08845808B422FFB360C2F6F5FB368CFB" box="[1176,1265,1987,2013]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the 
<emphasis id="13B7E573B422FFB26167F6F5FF2E8B96" italics="true" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ch. sub- sinuata</emphasis>
group for the peculiar feature of a pair of submedian humps at front of dorsal area; other diagnostic features are as follow: elongate shape of tergum III and subparallel malar spaces. The small and elongate black spots, shared with the Middle East green species, are unusual for this group; these concolor species possibly represent a separate subgroup.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
